Anonymous Wed 20 Oct 2021 21:45:08 No.42537398 Report
Quoted By: >>42540090
>>42536901
Fur's made up of spikes. They're a lot like scales in that way. You can get really intense with individually defining them (Dorohedoro did this I think), or really careful in your way of suggesting where they change from big spikes to small spikes or where the spikes change direction, like around the neck and shoulders. Generally, more, careful detail translates to denseness, and smudgey, undefined detail translates to smoothness.
I haven't done artist shit in more than a decade though, and that was highly amateur so my advice is probably shit. Maybe check out Nature of Nature's Art, since I think it's a well done, realistic, simple art style that's easy to reference for practice. Probably should find someone more qualified than me though.
